This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction and sentence-level entity embedding. Additionally, the paper proposes a neural network model for this task, which is a common approach in the field of computational linguistics. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) because the proposed model is based on neural networks and involves learning low-dimensional representations of entities. 

Furthermore, it may belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because relation extraction is a common task in information retrieval, and the proposed model could potentially be used to improve information retrieval systems. 

Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because the proposed model involves the use of neural networks and could be considered a form of evolutionary computing in the sense that it learns to represent entities in a low-dimensional space.
